article.headline: Alabama State 80, Tuskegee 77
article.story: MONTGOMERY, Ala. (AP) -- Andrew Hayles scored 20 points to lead Alabama State past Tuskegee 80-77 Friday night. The Hornets (1-2) made 14 of 14 attempted free throw shots in the first half to help lead them to a halftime lead of 43-30 over the Golden Tigers (0-2). The game's leading scorer was Tuskegee's Robert Helaire with 22 points. Hayles was the leading scorer for Alabama State, followed by Joel Bosh with 18 points, Dustin Richmond with 17 and Moses Edun with 10. Edun also had ten rebounds and Bosh had eight. Sean-Claude Terrell added to the Tigers' score with 14 points, and Keith Flournoy chipped in with 13 points. Down by 13 points after the first half, Tuskegee hustled to outscore Alabama State by 10 points in the second half. But the Hornets' first half lead was enough to secure a win by three points.
